loopy a simple KDE4 media player

recent plans is to add subtitle support. phonon-vlc( version 0.4 ) or 
phonon-mplayer backend is fine, phonon-gstreamer needs some time.

new features:
* display autodetected subtitiles ( need backend support )
* allow to load external subtitle
* basic audio channel ( need backend support)
* stay on top
* snapshot 

recent plans:
* remember user loaded subtitles
* auto download subtitles from internet
* effects ( backend support )
